{"name":"Mathlib.Probability.Martingale.OptionalStopping","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Probability.Process.HittingTime","Mathlib.Probability.Martingale.Basic"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.lean#L144-L221","name":"MeasureTheory.maximal_ineq","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.html#MeasureTheory.maximal_ineq","doc":"**Doob's maximal inequality**: Given a non-negative submartingale `f`, for all `ε : ℝ≥0`,\nwe have `ε • μ {ε ≤ f* n} ≤ ∫ ω in {ε ≤ f* n}, f n` where `f* n ω = max_{k ≤ n}, f k ω`.\n\nIn some literature, the Doob's maximal inequality refers to what we call Doob's Lp inequality\n(which is a corollary of this lemma and will be proved in an upcomming PR). "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.lean#L115-L136","name":"MeasureTheory.smul_le_stoppedValue_hitting","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.html#MeasureTheory.smul_le_stoppedValue_hitting","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.lean#L98-L108","name":"MeasureTheory.Submartingale.stoppedProcess","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.html#MeasureTheory.Submartingale.stoppedProcess","doc":"The stopped process of a submartingale with respect to a stopping time is a submartingale. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.lean#L89-L94","name":"MeasureTheory.submartingale_iff_expected_stoppedValue_mono","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.html#MeasureTheory.submartingale_iff_expected_stoppedValue_mono","doc":"**The optional stopping theorem** (fair game theorem): an adapted integrable process `f`\nis a submartingale if and only if for all bounded stopping times `τ` and `π` such that `τ ≤ π`, the\nstopped value of `f` at `τ` has expectation smaller than its stopped value at `π`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.lean#L72-L83","name":"MeasureTheory.submartingale_of_expected_stoppedValue_mono","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.html#MeasureTheory.submartingale_of_expected_stoppedValue_mono","doc":"The converse direction of the optional stopping theorem, i.e. an adapted integrable process `f`\nis a submartingale if for all bounded stopping times `τ` and `π` such that `τ ≤ π`, the\nstopped value of `f` at `τ` has expectation smaller than its stopped value at `π`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.lean#L45-L66","name":"MeasureTheory.Submartingale.expected_stoppedValue_mono","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.html#MeasureTheory.Submartingale.expected_stoppedValue_mono","doc":"Given a submartingale `f` and bounded stopping times `τ` and `π` such that `τ ≤ π`, the\nexpectation of `stoppedValue f τ` is less than or equal to the expectation of `stoppedValue f π`.\nThis is the forward direction of the optional stopping theorem. "}]}